The Wedding of Prince Jean-Christophe Napoléon, head of the former Imperial House of France and the son of Prince Charles Napoléon and Princess Béatrice of Bourbon-Two Sicilies, and Countess Olympia von und zu Arco-Zinneberg, daughter of Archduchess Maria Beatrice of Austria-Este and Count Riprand von und zu Arco-Zinneberg, (wearing the Savoy-Aosta Choker/Bandeau Tiara and her mother’s Wedding Earrings) at the Cathedral Saint Louis des Invalides in Paris on October 19th. The Prince and Princess Napoléon had a Civil Ceremony in the town hall of Neuilly-sur-Seine on the 17th, and a Ball at the Château de Fontainebleau.

Royal Guests and Relatives included the Archduke of Austria-Este (uncle of the bride) and Princess Astrid, Archduchess of Austria-Este, the Duke (uncle of the groom) and Duchess of Castro with Princess Maria Carolina and Princess Maria Chiara of Bourbon-Two Sicilies, Grand Duke Henri of Luxembourg, Crown Prince Pavlos, Princess Olympia, and Prince Phillipos of Greece with Nina Flohr, Princess Beatrice ofYork and Count Edoardo Mapelli Mozzi, the Duke and Duchess of Braganza, the Countess of Paris, Hereditary Grand Duke Guillaume and Hereditary Grand Duchess Stéphanie, Prince Felix and Princess Claire, Prince Louis, Prince Guillaume, Princess Sibilla, and Prince Jean of Luxembourg with Countess Diane de Nassau, Prince Laurent of Belgium, Princess Anne de Bourbon-Siciles, Prince Philip and Princess Danica of Serbia, Prince Philip and Princess Isabelle of Liechtenstein, Princess Margaretha of Luxembourg and Prince Nikolaus of Liechtenstein, Archduke Carl Christian of Austria and Princess Marie-Astrid de Luxembourg, Princess Maria of Bourbon-Two Sicilies and Archduke Simeon of Austria, Archduke Rudolf and Archduchess Marie-Helene of Austria, Princess Maria Annunciata of Liechtenstein. Princess Marie-Gabrielle de Nassau, Princess Maria-Laura of Belgium, Princess Maria Pia of Savoy and Prince Dimitri of Yugoslav, Prince and Princess Micheal of Greece, Princess Tatiana Radziwiłł, Prince Christian and Princess Alessandra of Hanover, Prince Charles-Henri de Lobkowicz and Princess Edouard De Lobkowicz, Count Nicolas Colonna-Walewski, Duchess Sophie of Württemberg, the Marquis and Marquise de Goussainville, and Count Nicholas von Bismarck.
